### 1. Crocodile Entity

This entity will store the details of each crocodile.

```json
{
  "entity_name": "crocodile",
  "entity_type": "data_entity",
  "attributes": {
    "id": "string",          // Unique identifier for each crocodile
    "name": "string",        // The name of the crocodile
    "sex": "string",         // The sex of the crocodile (e.g., Male/Female)
    "age": "integer",        // The age of the crocodile in years
    "weight": "float",       // Weight of the crocodile in kilograms
    "length": "float",       // Length of the crocodile in meters
    "date_added": "datetime" // The date the crocodile data was ingested
  },
  "relationships": {
    "user_filters": "crocodile_filter" // Relation to filter criteria if applicable
  }
}
```

### 2. Crocodile Filter Entity

This entity will store user-defined filter criteria.

```json
{
  "entity_name": "crocodile_filter",
  "entity_type": "data_entity",
  "attributes": {
    "id": "string",         // Unique identifier for filter
    "name": "string",       // Filter by name (optional)
    "sex": "string",        // Filter by sex (optional)
    "age": {
      "min": "integer",     // Minimum age for filtering
      "max": "integer"      // Maximum age for filtering
    },
    "date_created": "datetime" // Date when the filter was created
  },
  "relationships": {
    "crocodile": "crocodile" // Reference to crocodile entity for filtering
  }
}
```

### 3. Data Ingestion Orchestration Entity

This entity will handle the orchestration of the data ingestion process.

```json
{
  "entity_name": "crocodile_data_ingestion",
  "entity_type": "API_REQUEST",
  "attributes": {
    "id": "string",                     // Unique identifier for the ingestion job
    "api_url": "https://test-api.k6.io/public/crocodiles/", // The API endpoint to fetch data
    "last_run": "datetime",             // When was the last data ingestion
    "status": "string",                  // Status of the ingestion job (e.g., Pending, Completed, Failed)
    "parameters": {
      "filter_by_name": "string",       // If there's a specific name to filter the data
      "filter_by_sex": "string",        // If there's a specific sex to filter the data
      "filter_by_age": {
        "min": "integer",                // Minimum age to filter
        "max": "integer"                 // Maximum age to filter
      }
    }
  },
  "relationships": {
    "crocodiles": "crocodile" // Reference to crocodile entities created during ingestion
  }
}
```

### Data Consistency Considerations
- **Referential Integrity**: The **crocodile_filter** entity has a relationship with the **crocodile** entity, ensuring that filters can only refer to valid crocodile records.
- **Data Types**: Each attribute has a specific data type (string, integer, float, datetime) to maintain consistency and ensure accurate data.
- **Ingestion Parameters**: The ingestion orchestration entity includes parameters for filtering data during ingestion, allowing you to tailor the fetched data according to user needs.

